SA now has 4,996 cases of Covid-19, health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said on Tuesday. Speaking at a briefing, Mkhize said that there were also three deaths, taking the national total to 93. All three deaths were in the Eastern Cape. Mkhize said 185,497 tests have been conducted at this stage. There had also been 2,073 recoveries. Of the three new deaths, one was a 67-year-old male, another was a 70-year-old male, and the third a 79-year-old female. All had "underlying [health] challenges", said Mkhize.